Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Lesson 11 How to grow old\N\N如何安度晚年\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.50,0:00:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,First listen and then answer the following question.\N\N听录音,然后回答以下问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What,according to the author,\N\N根据作者的看法,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.07,0:00:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is the best way to overcome the fear of death as you get older?\N\N人们年长后,克服对死亡恐惧的最好办法是什么?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.15,0:00:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,oppress: v.  忧郁，压抑\N\NSome old people are oppressed by the fear of death.\N\N有些老年人因为怕死而感到烦恼.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.51,0:00:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,justification: n.  正当理由\N\NIn the young there is a justification for this feeling.\N\N青年人有这种感觉是情有可原的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.88,0:00:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Young men who have reason to fear that they will be killed in battle,\N\N有理由害怕自己会死在战场上的年轻人,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.25,0:00:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,may justifiably feel bitter in the thought,\N\N他们感到痛苦是可以理解的,因为想到，\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.21,0:00:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,cheat: v.  欺骗\N\Nthat they have been cheated of the best things that life has to offer.\N\N自己被剥夺了生活所能给予的最美好的东西.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.24,0:00:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But in an old man who has known human joys and sorrows,\N\N可是老年人已经饱尝了人间的甘苦,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.89,0:00:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and has achieved whatever work it was in him to do,\N\N一切能做的都做了,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.57,0:00:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear of death is somewhat abject and ignoble.\N\N如果怕死,就有点儿可怜又可鄙.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.07,0:00:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The best way to overcome it--so at least it seems to me--\N\N克服怕死的最好办法--至少在我看来是这样--\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.48,0:01:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is to make your interests gradually wider and more impersonal,\N\N就是逐渐使自己的兴趣更加广泛,逐渐摆脱个人狭小的圈子,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.53,0:01:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,ego: n.  自我\N\Nuntil bit by bit the walls of the ego recede,\N\N直到自我的围墙一点一点地倒塌下来,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.26,0:01:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and your life becomes increasingly merged in the universal life.\N\N自己的生活慢慢地和整个宇宙的生活融合在一起.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.29,0:01:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,An individual human existence should be like a river--\N\N个人的存在应该像一条河流,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.25,0:01:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,small at first, narrowly contained within its banks,\N\N开始很小,被紧紧地夹在两岸中间,aa\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.63,0:01:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and rushing passionately past boulders and over waterfalls.\N\N接着热情奔放地冲过巨石飞下瀑布.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.58,0:01:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Gradually the river grows wider,the banks recede,the waters flow more quietly,\N\N然后河面渐渐地变宽,两岸后撤,河水流得平缓起来,河水流得平缓起来,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.54,0:01:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the end, without any visible break,they become merged in the sea,\N\N最后连绵不断地汇入大海，\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.47,0:01:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and painlessly lose their individual being\N\N毫无痛苦地失去了自我的存在.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.86,0:01:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The man who,in old age can see his life in this way,\N\N上了年纪的人这样看待生命,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.76,0:01:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will not suffer from the fear of death,\N\N就不会有惧怕死亡的心情了,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.64,0:01:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,since the things he cares for will continue.\N\N因为自己关心的一切事物都会继续下去.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.09,0:02:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,vitality: n.  精力, weariness: n.  疲惫感\N\NAnd if,with the decay of vitality,weariness increases,\N\N再者,随着精力的衰退,老年人的疲惫感会增长,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.62,0:02:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the thought of rest will be not unwelcome.\N\N有长眠愿望未尝不是件好事.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.04,0:02:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I should wish to die while still at work,\N\N我希望工作到死为止,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.39,0:02:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that others will carry on what I can no longer do,\N\N明白了有人会继续我的未竟事业,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.47,0:02:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and content in the thought that what was possible has been done\N\N想到能做的事都做了,也就坦然了.\N\N